JELP GUIDELINES FOR GRANTING INTEREST SUBSIDY TO NEEDY STUDENTS W.E.F. 1ST September 2014.
JELP application shall be in AFs prescribed format; duly filled against each point is mandatory. All required documents must be attached with the application form. Incomplete application will be liable to reject without any notice and same will not be eligible for any interest grant of subsidy by AF. To avail the interest subsidy on study loan from Bank. Student must register (forms are available on website www.AFatf.org) him/her self under AF s JELP scheme within 3 months from the date sanction of Bank loan for study. The applicant must have secured minimum 50% or more marks in all the Board/ College/ University examination starting from standard 10th onwards till the last examination and special test etc. he/she appeared. Recommendation from AF Trustee or AF Chapter is mandatory along with application form; subsequently it will be verified by AF Office. Student shall have to submit his/her claim for interest subsidy in AF Mumbai Office along with his/her JELP registration number in every financial year during 1st April to 30th June. In any circumstances, claim submitted for the previous financial years will not be paid. Minimum 30 to 40 days are required to process application received in the AF, therefore, students are advised to keep patience.
SEED – SCHOLARSHIP( INTEREST FREE LOAN) GUIDELINES FOR GRANTING SCHOLARSHIP (INTEREST FREE LOAN) TO NEEDY STUDENTS w.e.f Sep.2014.
SEED application should be on AF prescribed form only and the reply against each point is compulsory.
In this case the student has to send the following documents : I-20 Letter from University, Copy of Passport page showing visa and immigration stamp. Copy of fees payment, if paid in advance.
The applicant must have secured 60% or more marks in all the Board / College / University examinations commencing from standard 10th onwards till the last examination / Special test etc. All required documents must be attached along with the application. Incomplete applications will be rejected and same will not be eligible for personal interview and financial assistance. Recommendation from AF or AF FCP/Patron member is a must and same will be verified by AF office. Application will be accepted by AF only between April to July of each year. Application for Finance Assistance will not be consider for student who has already taken admission for the course. Applicant must arrange and give documentary proof that he / she has already arranged at least 50% of the required TOTAL STUDY EXPENSES.. In case the student is going abroad for study, then the payment is to be released only after admission in the Institute.

2]. A valid mobile number to receive SMS based notifications/communications related to the online application, Admit card, Entrance Test Result, Admission Counselling etc till the admission process is over and subsequently, if admitted.
3]. A recent scanned passport size colour photograph (4.5cmx4.5cm) in "jpeg" format only (file size of scanned photograph should not be more than 100KB). Also keep ready all scanned education documents/certificate/mark sheets and testimonial in the jpeg/pdf format, but shall not be exceed 300kb each.
4]. Forms only be accepted by online mode with all the necessary documents / enclosures etc.
5]. AF Common Entrance Test (CET) will be in English and Hindi language, will be held at five centres i.e. Delhi, Jaipur, Chennai, Indore and Pune.
6]. No travelling allowance and stay arrangement will be provided by AF to student. They have to make their own arrangements for the same.
7]. Admission process comprises of a CET and interview. Due weightage is also given to past academic performance of a student. Therefore, filling up complete details of educational qualification is necessary. Students would be called for written test based upon academic performance. Further, student will be shortlisted for interview based upon written test and academic performance jointly.
8]. Final selection would be based upon aggregate of marks obtained in written test,interview and academic performance.
9]. After successfully filling online form for registration, you will get USERID and PASSWORD on your e-mail for further information. After registration go through your Email Id InBox or Spam Folder for Your Login Credentials.
10]. All admissions in AF are strictly based upon merit. Students and their parents are advised not do any canvassing for admissions.
11]. Only successful candidate will get an e-mail for admission. AF Centre will be allotted as per All India Rank (AIR) of aspirant and subject to vacancy in the respective centre where you have applied for.
12]. For any other queries w.r.t. AF CET, kindly refer our FAQ section.
13]. The Academic Committee decision will be final for admission in AF.
14]. Please do not press back or refresh button while filing your registration form.
15]. In case of any problem or need any assistance please call on support number between 10:00 am to 5:00 PM except Sunday.
